headline: JPMorgan Branch Build Out Tests Costs Funding And Long Term Returns
summary: JPMorgan Chase (NYSE:JPM) plans to open more than 160 new branches across over 30 states in the coming year. The bank also intends to renovate nearly 600 existing branches as part of a broader multi year growth plan. The expansion focuses on low to moderate income and rural areas, along with fast growing regions across the US. The initiative is expected to support hiring and broaden access to in person banking services nationwide. For a universal bank the size of JPMorgan Chase, this move...
